------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are your critiques of the given DT implementations, as
specified in Step 2.5?

1. In dtGood.c, DT_toString fails to check the return
value of DynArray_new for NULL, which fails our memory allocation best
practices.
2. In nodeDTGood.c, the function Node_toString is fully implemented,
however it is never used. When dtGood.c builds the string representation
of the tree in DT_toString, it ignores Node_toString and instead uses
its own custom mapping functions which rely on Node_getPath and
Path_getPathname.
3. In nodeDTGood.c, Node_hasChild requires a Path_T only to remove its 
string and cast away the const qualifier, which goes against
abstraction principles.
4. dtGood.c follows non-standard parameter ordering in helper functions 
such as DT_preOrderTraversal which does not place the destination 
parameter first.
5. dtGood.c and nodeDTGood.c uses varables before they may be defined 
or initialized (e.g. using variable ulChildID in DT_traversePath or 
ulIndex in Node_new and Node_free).
6. In Path.h, function Path_getComponent is declared but never used
outside the module. Therefore, it is likely Path_getComponent is a
helper method and should use the static qualifier.
------------------------------------------------------------------------